{"key":"processedPost-8723114","value":{"id":8723114,"first":8719366,"last":8723878,"when":1217858752,"utime":"08/04/08 05:05 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />I assume the humidity is high, especially since the cakes are very fluffy. but everyone says mist, and so i shall.</blockquote><br />Fuzzy cakes are not a sign of high humidity.<br />As said, air exchange and near saturation humidity are two of the biggest pinning triggers, with bright fluorescent light coming in close behind.<br />Lots of growers here are cultivating multiple species.&nbsp; The problem with those who only grow cubes is they can unknowingly give out bad advice, simply because cubes are so darn forgiving and seem to pin and fruit well, even when the grower does everything wrong.&nbsp; By adding some of the harder to grow species to your collection, you'll be able to fine-tune your procedures.<br />RR","title":"Re: Should I be misting fluffy cakes?"}}